  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Until now, the method autoOpenSecureChannel and autoPair from the SDK returned the same type of exception on connection lost and other APDU related errors.\n\nAfter merging https://github.com/status-im/react-native-status-keycard/pull/29 we will get a different exception type for the two situations. The steps to take in status-react are\n\n1. Update to the new react-native-status-keycard\n2. Verify that the following scenario still behave as designed:\n  a. wrong password during pairing\n  b. lost connection during pairing\n  c. invalidated pairing (card unpaired through different app, openSecureChannel fails)\n\n@yenda also mentioned that a workaround was implemented because of the current lack of separation between the two error conditions. We should be able to remove this after merging.",
